org.numenta.nupic.util

Class MethodSignature

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.util.Tuple
      • org.numenta.nupic.util.NamedTuple
        • org.numenta.nupic.util.MutableNamedTuple
          • org.numenta.nupic.util.MethodSignature
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Tuple>, Persistable

    public class MethodSignature
extends MutableNamedTuple

    Tuple type that allows the setting of method parameters while setting those parameters on this object - in the same statement.

    This class is handy to avoid instantiating new Tuples during highly iterative processes.

    Author:
    David Ray
    See Also:
    MutableTuple, NamedTuple, Tuple, #setParam(Object, int), Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • addParam

        public <T> T addParam(T t,
                      java.lang.String name)

        Special setter which allows the setting of fields within this object while specifying the parameters of a method's call site. It does this by returning the value that the #setParam(Object, int) method is called with. 

              public void someMethod(A a, B b) {}
      
      MethodSignature ms = new MethodSignature(2);
      
      A a = new A();
      B b = new B();
      someMethod(ms.addParam(a, "A"), ms.addParam(b, "B"));
      
      -- OR --
      
      public void someMethod(MethodSignature ms) {}
      someMethod(new MethodSignature(2).setParams(new String[] { "name1", "name2" }, value1, value2));
      
      -- OR --
      
      public void someMethod(Tuple t) {}
      someMethod(new MethodSignature(2).setParams(new String[] { "name1", "name2" }, value1, value2)));
        Parameters:
        t - the value
        name - the name of the parameter
        Returns:

      • setParams

        public MethodSignature setParams(java.lang.String[] paramNames,
                                 java.lang.Object... objects)
        Allows the setting of contents within this object in the call site of a method which takes an instance of this MethodSignature object.

        objects - the parameter values
